meanings.definition: To defeat in physical strength or power.
meanings.sent1: The smaller wrestler was outmuscled by his larger opponent.
meanings.sent2: The weightlifter outmuscled his competitors to win the championship.
meanings.sent3: The tiny ant outmuscled the big beetle in the strength competition.
meanings.sent4: The determined team outmuscled their opponents to claim victory.
meanings.sent5: The superhero outmuscled the villain in an epic battle.

meanings.definition: To overpower or outperform in a physical contest.
meanings.sent1: The sprinter outmuscled his rivals to cross the finish line first.
meanings.sent2: The boxer outmuscled his opponent with swift punches.
meanings.sent3: The cat outmuscled the dog in the race to the food bowl.
meanings.sent4: The determined team outmuscled their competitors to secure the trophy.
meanings.sent5: The athlete outmuscled the competition with sheer determination.
